# Loga Guest House — Production Implementation Plan

A luxury boutique guesthouse website for **Loga**, Sri Lanka. Built with Next.js 14 App Router, TailwindCSS, and Supabase. The aesthetic direction is **"Tropical Luxury Editorial"** — inspired by Cinnamon Hotels & Resorts, with a rich warm palette, Cormorant Garamond serif headings paired with DM Sans body text, immersive full-bleed photography, and breathing negative space.

---

## Proposed Changes

### Project Initialization

#### [NEW] Project root (`c:/Users/jasva/Desktop/project/LogaGuestHouse/`)
Bootstrap with `create-next-app` using the App Router, TypeScript, and TailwindCSS. Install all dependencies.

**Key dependencies:**
- `@supabase/supabase-js` + `@supabase/ssr` — Supabase client/server
- `@tanstack/react-query` — data fetching & caching
- `react-hook-form` + `zod` — forms & validation
- `framer-motion` — animations & transitions
- `react-day-picker` — availability calendar
- `swiper` — image gallery
- `lucide-react` — icon set
- `date-fns` — date utilities
- `react-hot-toast` — notifications
- `@stripe/stripe-js` + `stripe` — payment processing stubs
- `nodemailer` — email confirmations
- `next-sitemap` — sitemap generation

